<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
  <teiHeader>
      <fileDesc>
         <titleStmt>
            <title>Lodel/AEDRES ODD</title>
         </titleStmt>
         <publicationStmt>
            <p>Publication Information</p>
         </publicationStmt>
         <sourceDesc>
            <p>Information about the source</p>
         </sourceDesc>
      </fileDesc>
  </teiHeader>
  <text>
      <body>
<p>In this version, we start by specifying just the elements which
appear in the lodel schema, according to the list provided at <ptr target="http:/lodel.org/715"/>
</p>
<p>We supply an <gi>elementRef</gi> for each element required. In
addition, we must supply the module <ident>tei</ident> since this
provides declarations for the model classes used in element content
models (without these, most of our elements will wind up with no
attributes and with an EMPTY content model).</p>
<p>We suppress from this module those attribute classes which provide
attributes that don't appear to be used in the Lodel schema.</p>
<p>We modify the att.global element class to provide only
attributes xml:id, xml:lang, and rend.</p>

<schemaSpec ident="lodel" start="TEI">
<moduleRef key="tei" except="att.ascribed att.canonical att.declarable
			     att.declaring att.ranging att.dimensions 
			     att.breaking att.cReferencing att.datable
			     att.datcat att.fragmentable att.divLike
			     att.docStatus att.responsibility
			     att.editLike  att.internetMedia att.media
			     att.naming 
			     att.segLike att.source
			     att.sortable att.edition att.spanning
			     att.translatable"/>


<elementRef key="TEI"/>
<elementRef key="ab"/>
<elementRef key="abbr"/>
<elementRef key="affiliation"/>
<elementRef key="anchor"/>
<elementRef key="appInfo"/>
<elementRef key="application"/>
<elementRef key="author"/>
<elementRef key="availability"/>
<elementRef key="back"/>
<elementRef key="bibl"/>
<elementRef key="biblFull"/> <!-- ? needed for <availability> of born digital sources -->
<elementRef key="biblScope"/>
<elementRef key="body"/>
